<br>
Your automatic assumption that any Int caster rolling on that belt is planning to sell it is slanderous, insulting, and WRONG.  Try playing your Enchanter to level 50 (only 40 more to go) and you might be taken seriously by me when offering gear selection criteria.<br>
<br>
As to the statement that it's "not really that much better than a Spider Fur Belt", well, yes and no.<br>
<br>
Having a belt with the same AC as a Spider Fur Belt but 5 int instead of Hitpoints may or may not be a major upgrade.  It depends a LOT on the rest of your gear.  There are a great many Enchanters, even with extremely good gear, who have a startlingly low Int when configured for generic combat.  When routinely hunting for XP, for example, I have a buffed AC just over 750, but my INT only hits 185-190 even with Enlightenment.  I know guys with NToV gear who are even more extreme about sacrificing Int for AC.<br>
<br>
I would expect any Enchanter in my guild to consider carefully before putting his name in the hat for a roll on such a belt, since we take CAWU with EXTREME seriousness.  And if he won it he DAMN well better use it.  But I think it extraordinarily arrogant and selfish for meleers to deny the opportunity altogether.<br>
<br>
And yes, if he sold it, he'd be disguilded before he could hit "Accept" in the trade window. <p><img src="http://home.sprynet.com/~kubik01/eqpics/Project6.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/utunzell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tunzell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#330000>(12/4/01 12:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The way I see it.</span><hr size=1> If you're an over level 50 int caster and you haven't got your int over 200, you need some serious help, it's just to easy.  It's not so tough for us enchanters to get over 200 cha either with all the buffs we get.<br>
<br>
If I'm in a pick up group it's usually known that all items are up for grabs.  When I'm with friends and/or guildies it's ALWAYS need before greed.  Lady Lime is right, spider fur suits me just fine.  I too have watched this belt go to melee's and I think it's great when they get it.  I don't even consider it a hybrid item, 10 ac on a haste belt is pretty astounding for any melee until you get into dragon hastes.  I don't doubt that an int caster would wear it, but I personally think it would be much better served on a melee.<br>
<br>
Just my 2 cp's. <p><p style="line-height: 10%"><font face="Monotype Corsiva" color="#0000FF">&quot;A<font size="4">rmor
