<br>
SBoC may ONLY be 21% haste (like the FBSS) but the stats on it make it significantly better.<br>
<br>
I take your point that if every tank on a raid already has FBSS level haste, then it is only the AC people are fighting over and therefore casters should be allowed to roll.  If tanks don't already have FBSS level haste - then it should go to them instantly.  (Though with FBSS down to 2kpp on Saryrn - a 50+ tank without one must be practicing buddhism or something.)  Even still, I think generally the 10 extra AC will benefit a class that tanks as much as 5 extra INT will help a chanter.<br>
<br>
Cloak of Flames going to a chanter would be plain wrong.. /shudder<br>
<br>
Its a damn shame VI don't create more 'class specific' items at the high end game, as it would eliminate most of the loot squabbling, which from what I can see is divisive and unwanted.<br>
<br>
i.e.  Half of the best monk items in the game are ALL/ALL and have 100 mana on them, what is all that about.  =P<br>
<br>
Hiero cloak is definitely (IMNVHO) a caster item. Yes its nice, but for tanks Spider Fur is better, and costs virtually nothing in comparison.  (Argument for hybrids I guess, but realistically how much mana do Ranjors need =P )<br>
