<br>
Lemme make an analagy.  Let's say a 10ac, 10int, 50hp/mana, and 50charisma belt drops.  Now, an average equipped level 60 wizzie will look at that belt and say, &quot;Wow, that's a nice belt.  I need more int, I need more hp, I need more mana, it's got all 3!&quot;  That wizzie will say that would be a good belt for him, and he'd be right, if it's better than the belt he's wearing.  A chanter, however, will look at that belt and pitch a tent.  A very moist tent in fact.<br>
<br>
Now I ask you- who should that belt go to?  It's a good wizard belt, no one will disagree with that.  But the fact is, it's an incredibly good chanter belt.  It has &quot;give this to a chanter&quot; written all over it, and the chanter with the chubber drooling all over that belt would have every reason to be pissed at a wizzie claiming to want it based on NBG over a chanter.<br>
<br>
It's the same thing with this belt.  It's got 5int, sure, it's a somewhat good newbie belt for an int caster.  But, it has haste, sta, and ac on it which makes it one hell of a melee belt.  Sure, an int caster would like it.  A melee would cherish it as an incredibly good item.<br>
<br>
So don't be greedy and ask for this as a chanter.  You make me look bad. <p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
